
Beans
--------------------------------------------------------18

    #   Are instances created & managed by Spring Container

Configuration Metadata
--------------------------------------------------------18
    
    #   Beans, its instantiation & its wiring needs to be specified in
        Configuration Metadata
        
    #   Application Classes are assembled as Beans with the help of this Configurtion information
    
    #   Ways to configure  #19
        1.  XML Based
        2.  Annotation Based
        3.  Java Based        
        
Example : XML Based
--------------------------------------------------------

        <beans xmlns="http://www.springframework.org/schema/beans"...">
            <bean id="accountService" class="com.wiley.beginningspring.ch2.AccountServiceImpl">
                <property name="accountDao" ref="accountDao"/>
            </bean>
            <bean id="accountDao" class="com.wiley.beginningspring.ch2.AccountDaoInMemoryImpl">
                <!-- dependencies of accountDao will be defined here -->
            </bean>
        </beans>
        
Example : Annotation Based
--------------------------------------------------------  
        @Service("accountService")
        public class AccountServiceImpl implements AccountService {
            private AccountDao accountDao;
            @Autowired
            public void setAccountDao(AccountDao accountDao) {
                this.accountDao = accountDao;
            }
        }
        
        @Repository("accountDao")
            public class AccountDaoInMemoryImpl implements AccountDao {
        }

Example : Java Based    #20
--------------------------------------------------------

        @Configuration
        public class Ch2BeanConfiguration {
            @Bean
            public AccountService accountService() {
                AccountServiceImpl bean = new AccountServiceImpl();
                bean.setAccountDao(accountDao());
                return bean;
            }
            @Bean
            public AccountDao accountDao() {
                AccountDaoInMemoryImpl bean = new AccountDaoInMemoryImpl();
                //depedencies of accountDao bean will be injected here...
                return bean;
            }
        }